    <h2>JAMB: Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <details>
      <summary>1. How much is the JAMB registration form?</summary>
      <p>The cost of the JAMB form is <strong>₦4,700</strong>. This includes the ePIN and the official JAMB-recommended reading text. Additional charges may apply if paid through agents or banks.</p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>2. Can I register for JAMB myself online?</summary>
      <p><strong>No.</strong> Registration must be done at a JAMB-accredited CBT center. This ensures proper biometric data capture and secure, standardized registration. Self-registration is not accepted and may lead to disqualification.</p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>3. How do I check my JAMB result?</summary>
      <p>
        You can check your result using two methods:<br/><br/>
        <strong>Via JAMB Portal:</strong><br/>
        - Go to <a href="https://www.jamb.gov.ng" target="_blank">https://www.jamb.gov.ng</a><br/>
        - Click on “Check UTME Result”<br/>
        - Enter your registration number or email<br/>
        - Click “Check My Result”<br/><br/>
        <strong>Via SMS:</strong><br/>
        - Send <strong>UTMERESULT</strong> to <strong>55019</strong> using your registered SIM.<br/>
        - Standard SMS charges apply.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>4. How do I retrieve my JAMB registration number?</summary>
      <p>You can retrieve your JAMB registration number by logging into your JAMB profile via the official portal or by contacting the CBT center where you registered. Always ensure your login credentials are safely stored.</p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>5. When is JAMB reprinting starting?</summary>
      <p>JAMB reprinting typically begins <strong>a week before the exam</strong>. This allows candidates to check their specific exam date, time, and venue. You must reprint your slip from the JAMB portal or at your CBT center to get these details.</p>
    </details>
